claim.claim-text:
A method of transmitting a group trigger message to a group of machine type communication, MTC, devices based on a cell broadcast service, CBS, messaging system, adapted for a user equipment and the method comprises:
receiving a paging message comprising an indicator;
receiving a broadcast message in response to receiving the paging message;
determining a resource from the broadcast message in which the group trigger message is located based on the indicator; and
obtaining the group trigger message from the resource of the broadcast message, wherein in response to receiving the indicator, the UE determines from the broadcast message the resource which is not a system information block, SIB, reserved for a warning message.

A user equipment for transmitting a group trigger message to a group of machine type communication, MTC, devices based on a cell broadcast service, CBS, messaging system, comprising:
means for receiving a paging message comprising an indicator;
means for receiving a broadcast message in response to receiving the paging message;
means for determining a resource from the broadcast message in which the group trigger message is located based on the indicator; and
means for obtaining the group trigger message from the resource of the broadcast message, wherein in response to receiving the indicator, the UE determines from the broadcast message the resource which is not a system information block, SIB, reserved for a warning message.

A method of transmitting a group trigger message to a group of machine type communication, MTC, devices based on a cell broadcast service, CBS, messaging system, adapted for a base station and the method comprises:
receiving over a first interface a first message comprising an information element, IE, which indicates that the first message is intended for a group of MTC devices;
transmitting a paging message comprising a group trigger message indicator which indicates a resource in a system information block, SIB, for the first message; and
transmitting to the group of MTC devices over a cell broadcast channel a broadcast message comprising the first message which is embedded in the SIB of the broadcast message;
wherein the SIB is different from another SIB reserved for a warning message.

A base station for transmitting a group trigger message to a group of machine type communication, MTC, devices based on a cell broadcast service, CBS, messaging system, comprising:
means for receiving over a first interface a first message comprising an information element, IE, which indicates that the first message is intended for a group of MTC devices;
means for transmitting a paging message comprising a group trigger message indicator which indicates a resource in a system information block, SIB, for the first message; and
means transmitting to the group of MTC devices over a cell broadcast channel a broadcast message comprising the first message which is embedded in the SIB of the broadcast message;
wherein the SIB is different from another SIB reserved for a warning message.
